stom"}, "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 2, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "widely", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": "ltr"}, {"mode": "normal", "text": " ", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}, {"type": "link", "fields": {"doc": null, "url": "https://css-tricks.com/what-is-a-headless-cms/", "newTab": false, "linkType": "custom"}, "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 2, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "discussed", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": "ltr"}, {"mode": "normal", "text": " online, and for good reason. The web has become more complicated and with complexity comes the demand for developers to better structure their code. The rise of interface libraries like React and Vue are now the de-facto standard for building modern applications and traditional content management systems are often not designed to make use of them.", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": "ltr"}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"type": "link", "fields": {"doc": null, "url": "https://payloadcms.com/docs/getting-started/what-is-payload#why-payload", "newTab": false, "linkType": "custom"}, "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 2, "children": [{"tag": "h3", "type": "heading", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "Why Payload?", "type": "text", "style": "", "detail": 0, "format": 0, "version": 1}], "direction": "ltr"}], "direction": "ltr"}], "direction": "ltr"}, {"type": "paragraph", "format": "", "indent": 0, "version": 1, "children": [{"mode": "normal", "text": "The team behind Payload has been building websites and apps with existing content management systems and application frameworks for over a decade. We know what works and what doesn't about each of the existing solutions, and to this day have found